com.foreach.across.modules.entity.views.processors

Class SingleEntityPageStructureViewProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.foreach.across.modules.entity.views.processors.EntityViewProcessorAdapter
      • com.foreach.across.modules.entity.views.processors.SingleEntityPageStructureViewProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EntityViewProcessor

    @Component
 @Exposed
 @Scope(value="prototype")
public class SingleEntityPageStructureViewProcessor
extends EntityViewProcessorAdapter
    Builds the default page structure for a single entity page. Adds page title, sets page layout and optionally adds the entity menu.

    If setAddEntityMenu(boolean) is true, the EntityAdminMenuEvent will be published for the entity and the resulting menu will be added to the page.

    During postRender(EntityViewRequest, EntityView, ContainerViewElement, ViewElementBuilderContext), an EntityPageStructureRenderedEvent will be published containing the context of the entity that was the base for the page structure. This allows for event base extending of the page structure in case of associations being rendered.

    Since:
    2.0.0
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
